      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy testing was performed for simplified flow cases. Full manufactured-solution verification for the hemolysis transport equation was not completed. Required level reflects MRL 5 expectation for rigorous code verification."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be below 5% for all primary hemolysis QoIs across all five operating points. Richardson extrapolation applied on at least three systematically refined meshes. Asymptotic range confirmed (GCI ratio within 0.95–1.05).",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study was conducted. GCI values ranged from 4.2% to 11.7% across operating points; two points exceeded the 5% threshold. Asymptotic convergence was confirmed for three of five cases. Achieved level 3 reflects partial compliance with the discretization error requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions partially replicate VAD operating envelope. Flow rates and rotational speeds match nominal COU conditions, but blood analog viscosity and temperature were not fully controlled to clinical values in all experiments."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index predictions were compared against experimental measurements at five operating points. Mean absolute error was 38%, exceeding acceptable thresholds. Statistical comparison methods were applied but confidence intervals overlap only partially."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly computed from model outputs without surrogate mapping. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distributions) must be documented as supporting evidence. QoI relevance must be confirmed by a clinical subject matter expert.",
      "rationale": "NIH is computed directly from the CFD shear stress field using the Giersiepen power-law model. Clinical SME confirmed relevance of NIH as primary QoI. Secondary QoIs including shear stress distributions and residence time were documented. Achieved level 3 because SME sign-off was informal and not documented in a traceable review record."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic pump geometry, which matches the COU geometry. However, validation was performed at only two of five COU operating points, and blood analog rather than porcine blood was used. Extrapolation to remaining operating points introduces unquantified uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Solver residual tolerances were set to standard defaults. No iterative convergence study was performed to confirm that residual levels correspond to converged QoI values. Required level not achieved."
