      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen hemolysis power-law model was selected without systematic comparison against alternative models such as the Arora or Taskin formulations. Model form uncertainty was not quantified. Required level not achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must have documented sources with uncertainty bounds. Monte Carlo sampling must propagate input uncertainty through to QoI distributions. Sensitivity indices (Sobol first-order and total-order) must be computed for all inputs with coefficient of variation above 5%.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed with 500 samples. Input distributions were assigned based on literature ranges. Sobol sensitivity indices were computed for viscosity and power-law exponent but not for boundary condition parameters. Achieved level 2 because boundary condition uncertainty was not propagated."
    },
